name: trange
description: Filters data for the given time range using the @timestamp attribute.

params.name: start_time_or_offset
params.description: Offset from NOW for the single parameter mode. Start time for two parameter mode.  In two parameter mode, the start time value can be a date string, date, date_nanos or epoch milliseconds.

params.name: end_time

examples:
FROM k8s
| WHERE TRANGE("2024-05-10T00:17:14.000Z", "2024-05-10T00:18:33.000Z")
| SORT @timestamp
| KEEP @timestamp
| LIMIT 10

FROM k8s
| WHERE TRANGE(to_datetime("2024-05-10T00:17:14Z"), to_datetime("2024-05-10T00:18:33Z"))

| KEEP @timestamp
| LIMIT 10
